---
// Cookie Policy · Approved by Danish (CLO), 28 April 2026
// Calibrated to: UK GDPR, EU PECR (revised 2026), UAE PDPL Federal Decree-Law 45/2021.
// Tamazia's actual cookie usage at time of writing: only one first-party functional storage key
// ('tamazia-cookie-consent') for consent state. No analytics. No marketing pixels. No third-party trackers.
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/layout/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/layout/Footer.astro';
const lastUpdated = '28 April 2026';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy · Tamazia"
  description="How tamazia.co.uk uses cookies and local storage. Only essential first-party storage. No third-party trackers. No marketing pixels."
  noindex={false}
>
  <Header />
  <main id="main" class="legal-page">
    <article class="legal-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal · Cookies</p>
      <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Last updated: {lastUpdated}. This page tells you how tamazia.co.uk uses cookies and similar
        local-storage technologies. This site uses only essential first-party storage. No analytics, no
        advertising trackers, and no third-party cookies are set.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2>1. What is a cookie</h2>
        <p>
          A cookie is a small text file stored by your browser on your device when you visit a website.
          Local storage and session storage are similar mechanisms managed by your browser. Together
          these allow a site to remember information across page loads.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. The cookies and storage tamazia.co.uk uses</h2>
        <table class="legal-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Name</th><th>Type</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Duration</th><th>First / third party</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>tamazia-cookie-consent</code></td>
              <td>Local storage</td>
              <td>Remembers whether you accepted or rejected non-essential cookies on the consent banner.</td>
              <td>Persistent until cleared</td>
              <td>First party</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>
          That is the complete list at the time of writing. If we ever add analytics or any other category
          of cookie, this page will be updated and the consent banner will request fresh consent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. What we do not use</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>No Google Analytics, Plausible, Fathom, or any other analytics platform.</li>
          <li>No Meta Pixel, LinkedIn Insight, Twitter Pixel, or any advertising tag.</li>
          <li>No third-party tracking cookies of any kind.</li>
          <li>No fingerprinting, session replay, or behavioural profiling.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Your choices</h2>
        <p>
          When you first visit tamazia.co.uk you will see a consent banner with two equally prominent
          options: <strong>Reject non-essential</strong> and <strong>Accept all</strong>. Because the
          site only uses essential storage today, both options currently produce the same behaviour. If
          we add any non-essential storage in future, only the Accept option will allow it.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can clear your decision at any time by clearing site storage in your browser. The banner
          will reappear on your next visit and you can choose again.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Lawful basis</h2>
        <p>
          Under UK GDPR and EU GDPR the essential cookie used by this site is processed on the basis of
          legitimate interests under Article 6(1)(f). Namely, the operation of the consent mechanism
          itself, which is required by EU PECR and the UK PECR.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy: <a href="mailto:realfamemedia@gmail.com">realfamemedia@gmail.com</a>.
          For data-subject requests under UK GDPR / EU GDPR / UAE PDPL, see the
          <a href="/privacy">privacy notice</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <p class="legal-footer-note">
        This document is a plain-English summary of how tamazia.co.uk handles cookies and local storage. It
        is reviewed alongside the <a href="/privacy">privacy notice</a> and <a href="/terms">terms of
        service</a>. Material changes are versioned in the page header.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    background: var(--ivory);
    color: var(--oxblood-ink);
    padding: 80px 0 120px;
  }
  .legal-inner {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px;
    font-family: var(--ff-body, Inter, system-ui, sans-serif);
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.24em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold-text-strong, #5C3F18);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--ff-display, 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif);
    font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 52px);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
    color: var(--oxblood);
  }
  .lede {
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--oxblood-wine);
    margin: 0 0 48px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold);
    padding-bottom: 32px;
  }
  section { margin: 0 0 40px; }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--ff-display, 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 26px);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    color: var(--oxblood-ink);
  }
  p, li {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    color: var(--oxblood-wine);
  }
  ul { padding-left: 22px; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  a {
    color: var(--gold-text-strong, #5C3F18);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
  a:hover { color: var(--oxblood); }
  code {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: 14px;
    background: rgba(201, 167, 114, 0.18);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .legal-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 16px 0 24px;
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .legal-table th, .legal-table td {
    border: 1px solid rgba(90, 26, 43, 0.18);
    padding: 10px 12px;
    text-align: left;
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .legal-table th {
    background: rgba(201, 167, 114, 0.12);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--oxblood-ink);
  }
  .legal-footer-note {
    margin: 56px 0 0;
    padding: 24px 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(201, 167, 114, 0.4);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--oxblood-mist, #6D2037);
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .legal-page { padding: 56px 0 80px; }
    .lede { font-size: 16px; padding-bottom: 24px; margin-bottom: 36px; }
    .legal-table { font-size: 13px; }
    .legal-table th, .legal-table td { padding: 8px 10px; }
  }
</style>
